caption.p:
Schematics of cerebellar neurons and their circuitry in zebrafish (left) and
mouse (right). BC indicates basket cell; EC, eurydendroid cell; GC, granule
cell; GCL, granule cell layer; GoC, Golgi cell; ION, inferior olive nuclei;
MF, mossy fibre; ML, molecular layer; ON, octaval nuclei; PC, Purkinje cell;
PCL, Purkinje cell layer; SC, stellate cells; VN, vestibular nuclei.
